  "local_port": 52634,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some free alternatives to Aha.io?",
  "response": "Aha! is a popular product management and roadmapping tool, but there are several free alternatives that can help you manage your product development process. Here are some free options you can consider:\n\n1. **Trello**\n   - **Features**: Trello is a flexible project management tool that uses boards, lists, and cards to organize tasks. It\u2019s great for simple roadmapping and task management.\n   - **Pros**: Easy to use, highly customizable with power-ups, and integrates well with other tools.\n   - **Cons**: May not be as robust as Aha! for complex product management needs.\n\n2. **Asana**\n   - **Features**: Asana offers task and project management features that can be used for roadmapping and tracking product development.\n   - **Pros**: User-friendly interface, good for team collaboration, and offers a free plan with substantial features.\n   - **Cons**: Can become complex for larger teams, and some advanced features are behind a paywall.\n\n3. **Notion**\n   - **Features**: Notion is an all-in-one workspace that can be used for note-taking, task management, and even product roadmapping through customizable templates.\n   - **Pros**: Highly flexible, allows for custom roadmaps and databases, and has a free plan that's generous for individual users.\n   - **Cons**: Can have a steep learning curve due to its versatility, and some collaborative features are limited on the free plan.\n\n4. **Jira**\n   - **Features**: Jira is a powerful project and issue tracking tool that can be used for agile product development and roadmapping.\n   - **Pros**: Robust feature set for software development teams, integrates well with other Atlassian tools, and offers a free plan for up to 10 users.\n   - **Cons**: Can be overwhelming for non-technical teams, and the free plan has limitations.\n\n5. **Productboard**\n   - **Features**: Productboard offers product management and roadmapping features, with a free plan that includes basic functionality.\n   - **Pros**: Specifically designed for product management, easy to use, and integrates well with other tools.\n   - **Cons**: The free plan has significant limitations compared to paid versions.\n\n6. **ClickUp**\n   - **Features**: ClickUp is an all-in-one productivity platform that includes task management, roadmapping, and project tracking features.\n   - **Pros**: Highly customizable, offers a free plan with extensive features, and good for team collaboration.\n   - **Cons**: Can be overwhelming due to its vast feature set, and some advanced features are only available on paid plans.\n\nWhen choosing a free alternative to Aha!, consider your specific needs, the size of your team, and the complexity of your product development process. Each tool has its strengths and limitations, so it\u2019s important to evaluate which one aligns best with your goals.",
